#. <section class="sutta" id="sn42.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn42.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 42"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 42"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn42.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Gāmaṇivagga"
msgstr "1. Chiefs"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Tālapuṭasutta → puṭo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Tālapuṭasutta"
msgstr "2. With Tāḷapuṭa"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.307"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. VAR: tālapuṭo → tālaputto (s1-3, km) | talapuṭo (pts1)
msgctxt "sn42.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tālapuṭo naṭagāmaṇi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho tālapuṭo "
"naṭagāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Tāḷapuṭa the dancing master came up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to "
"one side, and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.3"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, pubbakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ naṭānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have heard that the dancers of the past who were teachers of "
"teachers said:"

# Re saccalika, I follow BB and the comm. even though “distortion of the truth” seems like a better meaning, sacca and alika always occur as a contrastive pair, supporting the comm.
msgctxt "sn42.2:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘yo so naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe saccālikena janaṃ hāseti rameti, so "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pahāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a dancer entertains and amuses people on a stage or at a festival "
"with truth and lies. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in the company of laughing gods.’"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.5"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.6"
msgid "“Alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ. Mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti."
msgstr "“Enough, chief, let it be. Don’t ask me that.”"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.7"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho tālapuṭo naṭagāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time …"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.8"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, pubbakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ naṭānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.9"
msgid ""
"‘yo so naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe saccālikena janaṃ hāseti rameti, so "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pahāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.10"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.11"
msgid "“Alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ. Mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.12"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho tālapuṭo naṭagāmaṇi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And for a third time Tāḷapuṭa said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.13"
msgid ""
"“sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, pubbakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ naṭānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have heard that the dancers of the past who were teachers of "
"teachers said:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.14"
msgid ""
"‘yo so naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe saccālikena janaṃ hāseti rameti, so "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pahāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a dancer entertains and amuses people on a stage or at a festival "
"with truth and lies. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in the company of laughing gods.’"

msgctxt "sn42.2:1.15"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: na labhāmi → nālatthaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn42.2:2.1"
msgid "“Addhā kho tyāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, na labhāmi:"
msgstr "“Clearly, chief, I’m not getting through to you when I say:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.2"
msgid "‘alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Enough, chief, let it be. "

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.3"
msgid "mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī’ti."
msgstr "Don’t ask me that.’"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.4"
msgid "Api ca tyāhaṃ byākarissāmi."
msgstr "Nevertheless, I will answer you."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.5"
msgid "Pubbe kho, gāmaṇi, sattā avītarāgā rāgabandhanabaddhā."
msgstr ""
"When sentient beings are still not free of greed, and are still bound by "
"greed,"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.6"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe ye dhammā rajanīyā te upasaṃharati "
"bhiyyoso mattāya."
msgstr ""
"a dancer in a stage or festival presents them with even more arousing things."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.7"
msgid "Pubbe kho, gāmaṇi, sattā avītadosā dosabandhanabaddhā."
msgstr ""
"When sentient beings are still not free of hate, and are still bound by hate,"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.8"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe ye dhammā dosanīyā te upasaṃharati "
"bhiyyoso mattāya."
msgstr ""
"a dancer in a stage or festival presents them with even more hateful things."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.9"
msgid "Pubbe kho, gāmaṇi, sattā avītamohā mohabandhanabaddhā."
msgstr ""
"When sentient beings are still not free of delusion, and are still bound by "
"delusion,"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.10"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe ye dhammā mohanīyā te upasaṃharati "
"bhiyyoso mattāya."
msgstr ""
"a dancer in a stage or festival presents them with even more delusory things."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.11"
msgid ""
"So attanā matto pamatto pare madetvā pamādetvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā "
"pahāso nāma nirayo tattha upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"And so, being heedless and negligent themselves, they’ve encouraged others "
"to be heedless and negligent. When their body breaks up, after death, they’"
"re reborn in the hell called ‘Laughter’."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.12"
msgid "Sace kho panassa evaṃdiṭṭhi hoti:"
msgstr "But if you have such a view:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.13"
msgid ""
"‘yo so naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe saccālikena janaṃ hāseti rameti, so "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pahāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’ti, sāssa "
"hoti micchādiṭṭhi."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a dancer entertains and amuses people on a stage or at a festival "
"with truth and lies. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in the company of laughing gods.’ This is your wrong view."

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.14"
msgid ""
"Micchādiṭṭhikassa kho panāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, purisapuggalassa dvinnaṃ gatīnaṃ "
"aññataraṃ gatiṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "An individual with wrong view is reborn in one of two places, I say:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:2.15"
msgid "nirayaṃ vā tiracchānayoniṃ vā”ti."
msgstr "hell or the animal realm.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.308"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn42.2:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, tālapuṭo naṭagāmaṇi parodi assūni pavattesi."
msgstr "When he said this, Tāḷapuṭa cried and burst out in tears."

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.2"
msgid "“Etaṃ kho tyāhaṃ, gāmaṇi, nālatthaṃ:"
msgstr "“This is what I didn’t get through to you when I said:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.3"
msgid "‘alaṃ, gāmaṇi, tiṭṭhatetaṃ; mā maṃ etaṃ pucchī’”ti."
msgstr "‘Enough, chief, let it be. Don’t ask me that.’”"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.4"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, etaṃ rodāmi yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evamāha;"
msgstr "“Sir, I’m not crying because of what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.5"
msgid ""
"api cāhaṃ, bhante, pubbakehi ācariyapācariyehi naṭehi dīgharattaṃ nikato "
"vañcito paluddho:"
msgstr ""
"But sir, for a long time I’ve been cheated, tricked, and deceived by the "
"dancers of the past who were teachers of teachers, who said:"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘yo so naṭo raṅgamajjhe samajjamajjhe saccālikena janaṃ hāseti rameti so "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pahāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose a dancer entertains and amuses people on a stage or at a festival "
"with truth and lies. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in the company of laughing gods.’"

# punctuation incorrect
msgctxt "sn42.2:3.7"
msgid "“Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.8"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo "
"pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.9"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.10"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.11"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho tālapuṭo naṭagāmaṇi bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the dancing master Tāḷapuṭa received the going forth, the ordination in "
"the Buddha’s presence."

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.12"
msgid "Acirūpasampanno ca panāyasmā tālapuṭo … pe …"
msgstr "Not long after his ordination, Venerable Tāḷapuṭa"

msgctxt "sn42.2:3.13"
msgid "arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn42.2:3.14"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
